The Telegraph - Calcutta : Bengal
		 Sunday, July 25, 2004  BRIEFS
				 																																	Malda, July 24: A paranoid youth today beheaded his 99-year-old neighbour with a sickle, claiming that goddess Kali had, in a dream, demanded human sacrifice to put an end to his troubles, reports a correspondent.				 																																	Police have arrested Debu Saha, 22, on the charge of murdering Gobinda Mandal in the Ratua police station area, 280 km from Calcutta. Sahas family was rendered destitute and landless by the land erosion by the Phulahar river.				 																																	Calcutta: Tariq Mohammad, 13, died of head injuries at SSKM Hospital on Saturday, after a concrete slab from a building fell on him when he was playing football in Garden Reach police station area, says a reporter.				 																																	Calcutta: The officer-in-charge of Madhyamgram police station, Bikashranjan De, has been suspended as quot;part of an administrative measure against slack officials quot;, reports a correspondent. Sources said the officer was suspended following a spate of dacoities.				 																																	Bongaon: One person has been arrested on charges of killing a woman after raping her in Bongaon. Arun Gayen of Kalupur village allegedly raped a 19-year-old neighbour on July 10, reports a correspondent. Her body was found the next day in a pond.				 																																	West Midnapore: Five persons looted Rs 70,000 in cash on Friday night from a petrol pump in Sheko, about 200 km from Calcutta. The dacoits locked the two guards in a generator room at the pump before looting the cash, reports our correspondent. 
